<br>
It's not because I don't want to see all of you with nice new weapons, it's a motivational issue. =(<br>
<br>
I'll try to knuckle down a little more, but 2 points an hour just SUCKS and I don't even want to think about how bad Nim has it comparatively.<br>
<br>
-Creepy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ukrystl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krystl</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(11/27/01 12:33:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=749.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trade skills</span><hr size=1> The purpose of having some money to invest in our trades people is to eliminate the need to do the consignments!  If you had more funds, you would not have to waste your time running all over creation. : )  I don't know exactly how much money would be needed to raise a 350 skill to 500 or so, I'm sure Nimitz would have somewhat of a better idea.  Power skilling would be the objective here, so hopefully the skills would raise much more rapidly. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Krystl</i>, Albion Cleric of Palomides<br>
<font size="2"><b>Proud leader of The Forgotten Truth in DAoC
<font size="1"><b><i>"Wait!  I'm lost!"</i></b></font> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uapo44.showPublicProfile?language=EN>apo44</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(11/27/01 5:32:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=749.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trade skill day 1</span><hr size=1> 2-3 points per hour, post 400 is about right running comsingments. Since i almost did no power leveling I don't know what the cost would be. I suggest that we give 50 gold to each trade. I am pretty shure we will get a fletcher to 500 with that much if (s)he make arrows up the wazoo. I don't know how far it would get AC'er or WPC'er but it should help them shave many hours from there task. For weapon crafter i say make studded glove till they turn green then boots. I know that once AC'er get near 500 I can make tailoring iteam at cost, then when the AC'er turn in his consinment he have a huge profit(2-15g in the 550+ range). So i suggest that we do 5-10 consingments and then power skill the AC'er with the profit. I am clueless about WPC'er, but i'll research the quickest path to power skilling on the boards.<br>
<br>
Nimitz<br>
<br>
P.S. most people i know use the tailor/ac'er combo to fund trades and guilds. fletcher and weapon crafter are left in the boonies when it comes to making huge money. <br>
